<div class="permissions-errors">The action you have requested is limited to users in the group: <a href="/wiki/index.php?title=GwenWiki:Users&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="GwenWiki:Users (page does not exist)">Users</a>.</div>
<p>You can view and copy the source of this page:
</p><textarea id="wpTextbox1" name="wpTextbox1" cols="80" rows="25" readonly="readonly">== Ωmni System to World of Darkness ==
I've decided to convert the old Second Edition World of Darkness setting over to the Omni System.

I can't express how much I love the first and second editions of the World of Darkness setting. But, I'm tired of the occasionally clunky rules system, particularly the way the game grinds to a halt once combat begins.

Talislanta has a wonderfully elegant rule system based around a single 20-sided die (generally agreed to be the inspiration for WoTC's 3E d20 system). This was codified by the now-defunct Morrigan Press into the universal &quot;Omni System&quot;. Morrigan Press went out of business, but you can still buy the Omni system rules (and their licensed genre games) from several sources, including online PDF purchase.

There's an [http://theomniverse.net/wiki/ Omniverse wiki] for fans of the Omni system.

The site [http://www.talislanta.com www.talislanta.com] is the official home for all things Talislanta.

=== WoD to Ωmni™ ===
If you're not starting a brand new game, probably the easiest way to switch to the Omni system is to take existing WoD characters and run them through a simple conversion process. 

If you're starting a new game from scratch, then, you'll want to create starting level characters using the Omni rules.

* Quick and dirty [[WoD to Ωmni System™ Conversions]] 
* A bit about Mages and [[Ωmni System™ True Magick]]
* Old but still useful, my [[Theme Handout for Mage]]
* [[Ωmni System™ Cyborgs]]
* The [[Talent Trees]] I'm working on.
* My working collection of [[Callings]].

I'm also working on converting NPCs in the back of the Mage:The Ascension 2nd Edition main rulebook, so that we have the stats of baddies for the players to face. There's not going to me much progress on this until I sort out the Callings.

== Ωmni Superheros ==

I have somewhat vague plans to come up with superhero a fan-based superhero set of supplemental rules for the Omni system.

Much of the reference material will probably be inspired by the old Villains and Vigilantes.

* [[Ωmni System™ Superhero Powers]]</textarea><div class='templatesUsed'>

